explanation: OS_NetworkGetID_Impl is required to assess whether the external low-level API call can be a dead code (unreachable or redundant). UT_Stub_RegisterReturnType, UT_ExecuteBasicHandler, and UT_Stub_GetReturnValuePtr are needed to analyze any testing or stub handling code that could be included in the build, which might also constitute dead code if never executed. These symbols help determine whether parts of the call graph associated with the target function are reachable or not, fulfilling the MISRA C rule about dead code.
